<h4 id="twitter-widget">Twitter Widget</h4>
<p>
	This widget can be included everywhere - in page builder and in a normal sidebar. For that widget we use normal WordPress <b>Text Widget</b>.
</p>
<p>
	First, go on <a href="https://twitter.com/settings/widgets" target="_blank">https://twitter.com/settings/widgets</a> and click <b>Create new</b>.
</p>
<img src="images/twitter-settings.jpg" alt="Twitter Settings" width="900" height="560">
<p>
	Now choose your Username, height of the widget, Theme and Link color. When you are happy with your widget click on Create widget button. You will get the code which you copy and paste in the Text Widget in your WordPress site.
</p>
<img src="images/twitter-code.jpg" alt="Twitter Code" width="900" height="600">